<p>phpBB has a few requirements which must be met before you are able to install and use it. In this section, these requirements are explained.</p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>A webserver or web hosting account running on any major Operating System with support for PHP</p></li><li><p>A SQL database system, one of:</p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="circle"><li><p>FireBird 2.1 or above</p></li><li><p>MySQL 3.23 or above</p></li><li><p>MS SQL Server 2000 or above (directly or via ODBC)</p></li><li><p>Oracle</p></li><li><p>PostgreSQL 7.x or above</p></li><li><p>SQLite 2</p></li></ul></div></li><li><p>PHP 4.3.3+ (&gt;=4.3.3, &gt;4.4.x, &gt;5.x.x, &gt;6.0-dev (compatible)) with support for the database you intend to use.</p></li><li><p>getimagesize() function enabled</p></li><li><p>The following PHP modules are optional, but will provide access to additional features.</p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="circle"><li><p>zlib Compression support</p></li><li><p>Remote FTP support</p></li><li><p>XML support</p></li><li><p>Imagemagick support</p></li><li><p>GD support</p></li></ul></div></li></ul></div><p> The presence of each of these required features will be checked during the installation process, explained in <a href="quick_installation.php" title="1.2. Installation">Section 1.2, “Installation”</a>. </p>